 able to replicate that experience again. He consciously tried it with othe=
r sankalpas later, but he either did not achieve mental focus (and the resu=
ltant rise of shakti) OR he totally forgot about the sankalpa by the time m=
ental focus was achieved and shakti could rise!
 
He realized one simple fa=
ct slowly. In the normal state of being, one has several sanklapas. But one=
 is unable to fulfil them due to the dispersion of mental energy in many di=
rections. In an elevated state of being where the mental energy is focused =
and sankalpas can be fulfilled, one can only think of sankalpas that Nature=
 wills one to have and forgets all other sankalpas one may have had before.=

 
